India's KL Rahul runs between the wickets. AFP/Phill Magakoe JOHANNESBURG - KL Rahul has been appointed new ODI Captain of India while Rohit Sharma continues nursing his hamstring injury. Rahul will take charge as Sharma bruised his leg in December. Sharma’s leadership campaign began after Virat Kohli was dropped before the start of the Tour. India's cricket board says Rahul will replace Sharma for the three-match ODI Series. Jasprit Bumrah will be vice captain.